and others) working in `{{ project_name }}`, a Ramboll **{{ service_kind }}**
service owned by **{{ owning_team }}**. {{ description }}

It is the vendor-neutral twin of `CLAUDE.md`; both point at the same binding
standards under `.claude/skills/`.

## Binding standards (read before editing)

The engineering rules for this repo live as skills in `.claude/skills/`. Apply
them on every change:

1. **`.claude/skills/property-based-testing/SKILL.md`** — every new pure function
   ships with at least one **Hypothesis** property test (idempotency, invariants,
   round-trip, metamorphic). Treat a shrinking counterexample as a real bug.
2. **`.claude/skills/python-clean-code/SKILL.md`** — small, single-responsibility,
   **fully-typed** functions with docstrings; guard clauses; no dead code; must
   pass `ruff`, `black`, and `mypy` clean.
3. **`.claude/skills/git-ci-governance/SKILL.md`** — `main`/`dev`/`staging`;
   branches named **exactly** `feature/<ticket>-<slug>`, `bug/<ticket>-<slug>`, or
   `hotfix/<ticket>-<slug>`; Conventional Commits; PRs into `dev` with review +
   CODEOWNERS + green Build/Test/Validate; CI references the **reusable workflows**
   only — never inline pipeline logic.

## Project layout

```
src/{{ package_name }}/   # pure, typed domain logic in core.py{% if service_kind == 'rest-api' %} + api.py (FastAPI){% endif %}

tests/                    # test_smoke.py + test_properties.py (Hypothesis)
docs/                     # MkDocs site (build with --strict)
.github/workflows/        # build/test/validate → reusable platform workflows
```

## Commands

```bash
pip install -e ".[dev]"{% if service_kind == 'rest-api' %} && pip install -e ".[api]"{% endif %}

pytest                # smoke + property tests
ruff check .          # lint
black --check .       # format check
mypy                  # types
mkdocs build --strict # docs
```

## Non-negotiables (summary)

- New pure function ⇒ at least one property test.
- Keep functions small, typed, documented; keep `ruff`/`black`/`mypy` green.
- Respect the branch model and naming; PRs go into `dev`.
- CI uses the reusable workflows — never copy pipeline logic into this repo.
